The National Agency for Food and Drug Administration and Control (NAFDAC) has called on state governments in the Northwest and Northeast zones to establish drug abuse control committees. A statement from the agency yesterday said this would tackle the high rate of abuse of codeine and other substances in the zones. The agency said youths were also the best resource of the zones even though it appeared the hope of many have been dashed by the menace of drug abuse. “The committees are to prevent the proliferation of drug abuse and psychotropic substances among the youth in addition to other activities that will reduce and eliminate drug abuse in the zones,” the statement said. The statement said that the agency has also has enlisted the support of religious leaders and clerics to convey messages to their congregation on drug abuse during the Ramadan sermons in various mosques across the zones.